      • authenticate

        protected HttpAccessControl authenticate​(java.lang.String userId,
                                         java.lang.String realm,
                                         byte[] password,
                                         CredentialStore store)
                                  throws HttpException

        Undertakes the authentication.

        This is separated out so that may be overridden to provide differing means for authentication.

        Parameters:
        userId - Identifier for the user.
        realm - Security realm.
        password - Password.
        store - CredentialStore.
        Returns:
        HttpAccessControl or null if not authenticated.
        Throws:
        HttpException - If fails communication with the CredentialStore.
